The paper deals with algorithmic solutions for verification, synthesis, and correction of concurrent systems, which are typically studied in the subfields of logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), distributed systems (cs.DS), software engineering (cs.SE), and formal languages (cs.FL). The use of monadic second-order logic (MSO) also suggests a connection to logic and formal languages.
